    • Constructor Detail

      • SquareChunk

        public SquareChunk(SquareRange range)
        Builds a SquareChunk with the given range and no mapping.

        The given SquareRange should have a strictly positive size. Giving a SquareRange instance with identical lower and upper bounds will result in a IllegalArgumentException being thrown.

        If the SquareRange provided has a range that exceeds Config.maxChunkSize , an IllegalArgumentException will be be thrown.

        Parameters:
        range - the range of the chunk to build
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if a SquareChunk cannot be built with the provided range.

      • SquareChunk

        public SquareChunk(SquareRange range,
                   Object[] a)
        Builds a SquareChunk with the provided SquareRange and an initial mapping for each long in the object array. The provided SquareRange and Object array should have the same size. An IllegalArgumentException will be thrown otherwise.

        The given SquareRange should have a strictly positive size. Giving a SquareRange instance with identical lower and upper bounds will result in a IllegalArgumentException being thrown.

        If the SquareRange provided has a range that exceeds Config.maxChunkSize, an IllegalArgumentException will be be thrown.

        Parameters:
        range - the range of the chunk to build
        a - array with the initial mapping for every long in the provided range
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if a SquareChunk cannot be built with the provided range and object array.

      • SquareChunk

        public SquareChunk(SquareRange range,
                   SquareIndexTFunction<T> initializer)
        Builds a SquareChunk with the provided SquareRange. The provided initializer generates the initial value of the element for each index. The given SquareRange should have a strictly positive size. Giving a SquareRange instance with identical lower and upper bounds will result in a IllegalArgumentException being thrown.

        If the SquareRange provided has a range that exceeds Config.maxChunkSize, an IllegalArgumentException will be be thrown.

        Parameters:
        range - the range of the Squarechunk to build
        initializer - generates the initial value of the element for each index.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if a SquareChunk cannot be built with the provided range.

      • SquareChunk

        public SquareChunk(SquareRange range,
                   T t)
        Builds a SquareChunk with the provided SquareRange with each long in the provided range mapped to object t. The given LongRange should have a strictly positive size. Giving a SquareRange instance with identical lower and upper bounds will result in a IllegalArgumentException being thrown.

        If the SquareRange provided has a range that exceeds Config.maxChunkSize, an IllegalArgumentException will be be thrown.

        Parameters:
        range - the range of the chunk to build
        t - initial mapping for every long in the provided range
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if a SquareChunk cannot be built with the provided range.
